Japanese Sold Net 2221.5 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-10-13T23:54:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/japanese-sold-net-2221-5-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended Oct. 7 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 2221.5 billion yen ($28.9 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 85.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 24.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 2111.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 231.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 59 billion yen in stocks, and sold 5.6 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 166.8
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  